24th Road (foreground, not shown), east of 21st Street (left, not shown), showing Fairbanks' old water tower (erected by Ed. Woolsey) in back of old 41 Cedar Place (now 24th Road). In the background are seen the rears of homes facing on TYwenty-fourth Ave.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
